caption.text:
That's why I'm trying, to be (the real) me...
.
When I was a child, I drew my dream to become an astonishing professor.. I forced myself to love sciences and forged my heart as firm as scientists used to be. But I found nothing, still big hollow on my heart. Those habit even completely change myself to become unaware of others and a bad person--too selfish, too many unreasonable queries.. just because I'm trying to be the cover of my dad's book.
.
I was so happy and cheerful outside, but still alone inside. Nobody can figure out the real me, because I was so smart to conceal myself, even to me.
.
But my recklessness, foolishness, and deceitfulness had brought me to the bottom of the life struggle, those multi-faceted personality finally were cracking my heart to start live like a human.
.
Those times were so hard for me, I against my dream, so blur, so dark, and sometime so sick. I start study social, hoping one day I can heal my soul, and find my inner peace--so I can start my live with a love.
.
Today I'm just twenty, so fast... Here I found my real passions, writing and drawing--the real me that I always try to cast to gain quality time with sciences before. I don't know that time flies so fast, I even feel just start my new dream and now seem I'm nearly to the final round...
.
Those hurdles had tought me to do everything better now, that it is a must to use my heart for every work, even for a competition or just help my friends... It is not a magic that it seem so easy for me to do sth, because there are many times behind just to live like a normal
.
Just wanna say, Love yourself when you have time... .
Thanks guys @dwi_mdpp @josephnaga... for always be three musketeers...
.
And my xoxo
@caesar.gabriel @dettasinaga @sanitaayu @nurishisyam  for always supporting me...
